In a small #pot, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. Fluff rice with a #fork.

Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @Green Bell Pepper{1}(cored, deseeded, and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Halve @Celery Sticks{2.5%oz}(halved lengthwise), then thinly slice crosswise. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%oz}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced) into ½-inch pieces.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a medium #pot over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and add @Flour{2%tablespoon}; cook, whisking constantly, until lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Whisk the roux constantly to avoid burning.

Once roux is finished, stir in bell pepper, celery, onion, garlic, and @Salt{1/2%tsp} until combined. Increase heat to medium high. Cook, stirring often, until veggies are softened, about ~{5%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl, combine @Veggie Stock Concentrate{2} and @water{2 1/2%cups}.

Once veggies are softened, gradually stir in stock mixture until smooth. Add mushrooms, tomato, @Kidney Beans{13.4%oz}(drained and rinsed), Blackening Spice{1%tablespoon}, @Dried Thyme{1%teaspoon}, and @Salt{1/2%tsp}. Stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer and cover pot. Cook, until veggies are tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @Collard Greens{3%oz} and @Salt{1/4%tsp} to pot with gumbo. Stir to combine.

Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, until collards are tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until butter melts. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide gumbo between #bowls{}. Top with a mound of rice and serve.